# Product language and direction (strict)

## Must
- All user-facing UI text must be **Hebrew only** (headings, buttons, labels, nav items, helper text, errors, empty states, aria-labels).
- The UI must be **RTL everywhere**.
  - Keep `dir="rtl"` and `lang="he"` in `index.html`.
  - Keep MUI theme `direction: 'rtl'`.

## Never
- Do not ship English UI strings.
- Do not add emojis to UI text.
- Do not write comments in Hebrew. If a comment is necessary, write it in English (or remove it).

## Enforcement checklist (before finishing any UI task)
- Search for new strings and ensure they are Hebrew.
- Check RTL alignment in common layouts (Navbar, forms, dialogs, tables).

